message: Pembrook said although no data encompass all human trafficking in the area, growing numbers of victims, some who worked in agriculture, are coming forth to report cases of servitude.  She said the key is knowing what to look for and understanding the sensitive situations of victims.

data.description: Some stereotypes, such as human trafficking being an immigration issue, do not apply completely in Santa Cruz.  Cases of immigrants being trafficked happen, but they are rare.
data.title: Santa Cruz, Monterey counties still hubs for human trafficking
